caption: Love this place!!!! The cornbread! The cornbread! The chicken sandwich is my favorite! Did I mention... THE CORNBREAD!!! DELICIOUS!!!!😋😋🤫

I love the food. It’s always amazing. Delivery service is not organized. I ordered through their website to support the business off Grubhub/Uber.. They ran out of short ribs for my order. They never called me, I had to called them. The food took over an hour. Just use the delivery apps because then you can have some recourse for that.

Absolutely the best chicken spot I've ever been to. These take pride in their work and it shows. The green sauce is incredible, the spices on the chicken are on point, and absolutely hands down the best corn bread I've ever tasted.
Beat chicken around, hands down

First time customer but won't be a last. The food here is really good.  My family and I tried a few different things: * The rotisserie chicken combo - I don't eat chicken but my family said it was good. They did mention the chicken was slightly on the salty side. The sides, roasted potatoes and rice, were delicious.  * Short rib sandwich combo - It was really good. The beef was cooked to perfection. I enjoyed the quinoa salad on the side. I did not like the cole slaw only because it did not taste fresh. I had to scrape it off my sandwich. And I couldn't eat the side order of it.  * Vegetable Terrine - It is absolutely delicious! It was my favorite thing ordered.  * Cornbread (comes with the combos) - Delicious. Moist and flavorful.  * Bread pudding - Omgnesss. Delicious!  I would recommend this place and can't wait to return.
One of the best rotisserie chickens you'll find! Excellent sides too, glad it's in the neighborhood!
Great chicken sandwich!

Always absolutely delicious! They are kind and top quality food and service. Thank you :)

My husband and I LOVE Lula Bird! We live in Downtown Brooklyn  and are always interested in finding restaurants with flavorful and healthy food options. We came across Lula Bird on Doordash and are hooked! The chicken is beautifully seasoned and the sides are all delicious and filling. Oh and the cornbread- it is soooo amazing that both my husband and I crave and dream about it!!!! I recently got an opportunity to communicate with the owner and am impressed with his commitment to superior customer service.  Lula Bird, you have earned 2 new loyal customers! Sincerely,  Jordan M & Safia
Hour wait for food

Delicious. Healthy. Very Keto-friendly.  Soul Food meets the Middle East? Some of the spices have a Moroccan or Lebanese flair.  I’ve been in quarantine, and am on the Keto diet, so I’ve been sampling many non-breaded chicken places. Out of about six places in Brooklyn all found on Dinner Dash, this place has the tastiest, most moist chicken, amazing sauces, and really great sides. Many people seem to love the collard greens—those aren’t for me, but the fried broccoli and cauliflower are very specifically seasoned, with a perfected texture. They are quite fatty sides, but beside a lean meat like chicken, it’s great. Apparently the best thing on their menu is the corn bread, but that is very not Keto, so I haven’t tried.  Thanks guys, for helping me stay Keto even during quarantine. The only thing I’d like to know is, what’s in the cauliflower (curious about carbs), and also, why only Wednesday????? THAT DISH IS LIFE ;)
delicious juicy chicken, great well seasoned sides and yes, the cornbread is worth all the hype.
The best corn bread in the world I’d pay to know the recipe
OMG the freakin chicken!!The corn bread and sweet potato purée...etc 100% about the tender,juicy chicken .

caption: I was so disappointed with this meal. I thought I was going to have as fresh, healthy, tasty and boy was I disappointed. Now I did see the negative reviews but I decided to give them a chance. I ordered the quarter chicken with 2 sides which were The fried cauliflower and the quinoa and a portion of cornbread. The fried cauliflower was horrendous. It was super soggy. Quinoa was okay— a bit on the dry side. The cornbread was tasty which was the best part of the whole meal. The chicken was tasty but I was surprised at how salty it was. For half the price, I could’ve just ordered from my local Dominican spot. Maybe it was a fluke meal? Don’t know but probably not ordering from them again.

I hate the word moist but this chicken was MOIST!!!!! So tasty, flavorful side delicious. Not dried out at all. The sides of collard greens and sweet potatoes were insanely good and the sauces (we got curried peanut, harissa, and green sauce) were the cherry on top. Just moved to BK and this will be a go to delivery meal for me, for sure! So happy I found them on Uber Eats.

Okay, so all those reviews about the cornbread tasting above and beyond delicious were absolutely on the money! It was the only part of the meal with flavor, however. It really was  the only redeeming aspect to the rest of my dinner though... While the chicken, roasted potatoes, and greens were all cooked perfectly, compared to the 🌽 🍞, everything else thst came with my dinner overall just tasted mostly bland, or under-salted & under-seasoned. Definitely would still recommend  enjoying  any of their combo dinners from here sometime! (Like next time you're too busy or tired to cook yourself...) Or if only simply to score that free piece of cornbread included with each meal

The bread pudding was PHENOMENAL. It was a great place to sit in and work too, but it is a small space. The woman at the counter was really nice and the food smelled amazing. The lunch specials are pretty large looking (I only have been once but I will definitely return).

Ordered delivery via Seamless last night. The delivery was quick - about 35 minutes. The food was excellent! Ordered 1/2 chicken with Mac and cheese, collard greens, Brussels sprouts and corn bread. Each side was great. As a southerner I appreciate good cornbread. It was different from what I expected but fantastic! I will definitely order again.

The rotisserie chicken is GOOD, as are basically all the sides I’ve tried (most of them). The potatoes are always great, and the green sauce can’t be beat. But this restaurant is so, so expensive for what it is—you can get a good rotisserie chicken from a grocery store for probably less than half the price they charge, and Lula’s chicken is not superior enough to merit the price difference. Also, they sometimes stop delivering or taking orders early because “it was busy that day.” Personally, I find this to be pretty unacceptable, especially considering that the prices border on highway robbery for relatively simple dishes. Simply put, service should be better at these prices.

I called to ask if the grubhub delivery would take long, trying to find out if it was busy and also if my address was too far—even though I was able to order from Grubhub and it estimated 30-40 mins. I got the nastiest human being on the phone...immediately began yelling to me about how the only way for me to make a delivery order is over seamless or Grubhub and interrupting me before I could finish my one and only question. I have waitressed in NYC for five years, I’ve never spoken to a customer like this right off the jump.  TLDR: (too long didn’t read?)
